<item>
            <title>[DERBY-476] Derby UI plug-in version 1.0.0 incompatible with Eclipse 3.1 M6 or higher</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-476</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Per this email thread:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-user/200506.mbox/%3c20050606165347.40256.qmail@web81302.mail.yahoo.com%3e&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/db-derby-user/200506.mbox/%3c20050606165347.40256.qmail@web81302.mail.yahoo.com%3e&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Derby UI plugin throws an exception when trying to start the Derby network server with Eclipse 3.1M6 or higher.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix for this is simple, and involves only changing a class name in 4 files per the email above.  Eclipse 3.1 is now GA so this fix should be made to the UI plug-in which will allow it to work with the current release of Eclipse.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, by adding this fix the plug-ins will no longer work with 3.0.x through 3.1M5 builds of Eclipse.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
